<document>
	<title>Round table discussion--treatment of lower respiratory tract
   infections with co-trimoxazole.</title>

	<author>Hughes-D-T.</author>
	<author>Pines-A.</author>
	<author>Percival-A.</author>
	<author>Stille-W.</author>

	<source>J-Antimicrob-Chemother. 1979 Nov. 5(B). P 207-19.</source>

	<abstract>Over one thousand patients with acute and chronic chest infections
   have been treated with a combination of trimethoprim and
   sulphamethoxazole.  The patients may be divided into four groups and
   the results are summarised in this presentation.  Much of the work
   is published elsewhere.</abstract>

